  "prompt": "What is the legal history of money laundering prohibitions?",
  "response": "The legal history of money laundering prohibitions is complex and has evolved significantly over time. Here's an overview of key developments:\n\n1. Early Origins:\n- Informal money concealment practices existed for centuries\n- Initial focus was primarily on tax evasion and hiding criminal proceeds\n\n2. United States Developments:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (1970) - First major anti-money laundering legislation\n- Established reporting requirements for financial institutions\n- Required documentation of large currency transactions\n\n3. International Expansion:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) established in 1989\n- Developed international standards for combating money laundering\n- Created recommendations for global financial transparency\n\n4. Key Legislative Milestones:\n- US Money Laundering Control Act (1986)\n- USA PATRIOT Act (2001) - Significantly expanded anti-money laundering regulations\n- Enhanced international cooperation and surveillance mechanisms\n\n5. Modern Legal Framework:\n- Comprehensive regulations covering multiple financial sectors\n- Increased criminal penalties\n- Robust international information sharing protocols\n\n6. Ongoing Evolution:\n- Continuous adaptation to emerging financial technologies\n- Increasing focus on cryptocurrency and digital transaction monitoring\n\nThe legal framework continues to develop in response to changing financial technologies and criminal strategies.",
